lor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Now I=
 fully recognize my own biases, too. I&#8217;ve deployed venture money for =
the first time during this post-COVID bull run, am long crypto, and am gene=
rally bullish and optimistic on technology. I would stand to benefit financ=
ially and reputationally from prices continuing to go up. I even believe th=
at reading about tech companies is less exciting for people in a bear marke=
t (unless I pull a heel turn and start writing salacious stories about comp=
anies crashing, which I won&#8217;t), so <strong>Not Boring and I would ben=
efit from the market partying like it was 2020 every year.&nbsp;</strong></=
p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 1em 0;">But I&#8217;m the first to admit <strong>I have no idea what&#82=
17;s going to happen.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">During the bull run, there=
 seemed to be a constant chorus of bears arguing that prices would come bac=
k down to earth; this bear market (a pullback of more than 20%) seems to be=
 a lot more one-sided.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">That&#8217;s not to say that bears=
 are wrong. In fact, I wouldn&#8217;t be surprised if they&#8217;re all rig=
ht and everything goes back to selling off after this little bear rally.&nb=
sp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 1em 0;">I just also wouldn&#8217;t be surprised if the market bounc=
es back and keeps growing.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The only thing I&#8217;m prett=
y sure about is that <strong>large groups of people all agreeing about some=
thing as complex and dynamic as the market are almost always wrong</strong>=
=2E&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a;=20=
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The general bearish certainty feels like the kind of si=
gnal that Medallion would feed on. Abstract away all of the underlying stuf=
f and just look at how the humans are behaving.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">With ever=
yone agreeing on a sustained crash, predicting the opposite was <strong>so =
simple a human could do it</strong>. On <strong>March 15th, at 10:52am ET</=
strong>, a friend who wishes not to be named texted:&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><str=
ong>&#8220;I also think we&#8217;re nearing a bottom. Just based on the amo=
unt of midwit tourists prognosticating about impending doom.&#8221;</strong=
>&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 1em 0;">He called the local bottom almost down to the hour.</p>=
